# Agent delegation

- Assume **one primary role** per turn unless the user asks for a multi-role review; see `AGENTS.md`.
- Before sizable features: read `docs/context/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`, `docs/context/TEAM_PLAYBOOK.md`, and relevant `docs/references/*.md`.
- End substantive work with: **done means**, files touched, and **verification** (`npm run format:check && npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm test`).
- If behavior or persistence changes: update `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` or add/update `docs/decisions/*.md`.
- Prefer **vertical slices** (UI + domain + tests) over non-integrating layers.
- **Git / caveman-commit**: Read **`skills/caveman-commit/SKILL.md`** for every commit message and for **`npm run ship -- '<msg>'`** (`docs/context/GIT_WORKFLOW.md`). **`pre-push`** runs **`git add -A`** and **blocks `git push`** until uncommitted work is committed; **`/caveman-commit` still runs in Cursor only** (hooks cannot invoke the skill). After **substantive code changes**, if the user did not say to skip git, end with a **caveman-style message** in a fenced code block and (when push is in scope) `npm run ship -- '…'` or `git commit` + push. Same for **`/caveman-commit`** or staging. Do not run `git commit` unless the user explicitly asks. No auto-commit on save.
